Model Details

The Einstein Lookalike Segments model identifies individuals who look and act like the target audiences for a give tenant by using these training algorithms, parameters, fairness constraints, and features.

Person or Organization

Salesforce Data Cloud

Model Date and Version
Pilot release March 2023
Target GA June 2023
Minor changes can occur throughout the release
Major changes can occur and are communicated via release notes
Model Type

Semi-supervised learning, Locality-sensitive Hashing algorithms

General Information

The Lookalike Segments model in Data Cloud identifies segments that look and act like the target audiences for a given tenant. The model is built on segments based on individual objects or unified individual objects as configured by your organization. Each seed segment has its own model trained to generate lookalike users. The model is refreshed regularly. The model processes Data Model Objects in Data Cloud for a given tenant, and automatically extracts features for model training. Each customer can have different Data Model Objects configured, resulting in different feature sets used in modeling. The model processes both profile and engagement data. The model is trained on semi-supervised learning and locality-sensitive hashing. It’s used to score each individual object or unified individual object outside of the seed segment. You can filter the output table based on similarity to score to generate lookalike segments for a desired reach. Two similarity reach boundaries are produced - the boundary value between similarity High and Medium and the boundary value between similarity Medium and Low.

License

The Lookalike Segments model is available to Salesforce Data Cloud customers with any of these editions, plus the Segmentation and Activation Add-on license.

Corporate Edition
Enterprise Edition
Enterprise+ Edition
